pair A, B, C;

A = (0,0);
B = 5*dir(40);
C = (5,0);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, N);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$13$", (A + B)/2, NW);
label("$10$", (B + C)/2, NE);
label("$40^\circ$", (1,0.4));
label("$100^\circ$", (4,0.4));
[/asy]

The two possible values of $\angle B$ are $\boxed{80^\circ}$ and $\boxed{60^\circ},$ so the sum is $80^\circ + 60^\circ = \boxed{140^\circ}.$

