O = (0,0);
Z = 0.4*dir(52.5);

dot("$O$", O, NE);
dot("$z$", Z, dir(75));
dot("$\frac{1}{2} a_1 + \frac{1}{2} a_2$", (A + B)/2, S);
dot("$\frac{1}{2} a_1 + \frac{1}{2} a_3$", (A + D)/2, W);
dot("$\frac{1}{2} a_1 + z \sin (\theta/4) \cos (3 \theta/4) + i z \sin (\theta/4) \sin (3 \theta/4)$", (A + F)/2, dir(0));
[/asy]

Thus, the area of $P$ is equal to the size (modulo a factor of $\frac{1}{4}$) of the sum of the parabolic segments defined by the four possible choices of $\theta.$

[asy]
unitsize(2 cm);

draw((0,0)--(2,0));
draw((0,0)--(1,1.732));

draw((-1.5,0)..(-0.591,0.655)..(0,1.732));
draw((0,1.732)..(1.026,0.495)..(2,0));
draw((-1.5,0)..(0,1.732)..(2,0));

label("$\theta$", (1.8,0.7));
label("$\theta/2$", (-0.75,0.9));
label("$\theta/4$", (0.5,1.5));
